---
title: Persons Table - Sirius Case Management
layout: layouts/fullwidth.njk
---
<h1 class="govuk-heading-l">{{title}}</h1>
<p class="govuk-body-l"> The persons table includes data on people within the Sirius system. It contains both LPA, Guardianship and Supervision data, as well as data relating to persons who are informed parties.</p>
<p class="govuk-body"><strong>Stability:</strong> The persons table is to be considered <strong>unstable</strong> and likely to change due to ongoing development work.</p>

<table class="govuk-table govuk-!-font-size-16">
      <caption class="govuk-table__caption govuk-table__caption--m">Persons table columns</caption>

   <thead class="govuk-table__head">
    <tr class="govuk-table__row">
        <th scope="col"  class="govuk-table__header">
            Column Name
        </th>
        <th scope="col"  class="govuk-table__header">
            Character Maximum
        </th>
        <th scope="col"  class="govuk-table__header">
            Is Nullable
        </th>
        <th scope="col"  class="govuk-table__header">
            Default
        </th>
        <th scope="col"  class="govuk-table__header">
        Constrained values
        </th>

    {% for column in persons.columns %}
    <tr>
        <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header">
            {{ column.column_name }}
        </td>
        <td class="govuk-table__cell">
            {{ column.character_maximum_length}}
        </td>
        <td class="govuk-table__cell">
            {{ column.is_nullable }}
        </td>
        <td class="govuk-table__cell">
            {{ column.column_default}}
        </td>
        <td class="govuk-table__cell">
            {% for ref, refclass in persons_refdata[column.column_name] %}
            {{ ref }},
            {% endfor %}
        </td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
</table>       